author: by worldengine
commands: ['"Alexa, launch Fidget Spinner."', '"Alexa, open Fidget Spinner."', '"Alexa, load Fidget Spinner."']
description: Fidget Spinner is a fun game based on the popular stress relief toy. Choose your spinner and special ability. Alexa will spin the fidget and tell you the number of spins. If the number is high enough, you can unlock higher levels with new spinners and new abilities. The game has ten levels with dozens of different spinners and abilities to choose from. To begin playing say, "Alexa launch Fidget Spinner."
title: Fidget Spinner

author: by The Magic Door, LLC
commands: ['"Alexa, open the magic door"']
description: The Magic Door is an Alexa-powered interactive adventure game with original stories. You can tell Alexa what choices to make as you navigate a forest, a garden, or an ancient temple. You can find hidden items, solve riddles, and help magical creatures. You can also find magical items to get a prize!Our current stories are:1. Help the Princess find her Crown in and beyond the Garden2. Find the Rabbit's Eggs beyond the Garden Gate3. Help the Gnome find his key in the Forest4. Save the Monkeys on the Tropical Island5. Enter a hidden Portal to an Ancient Temple6. Concoct a Potion for a magical Fern to the Wizard's Tower7. Search for the Wise Wizard in his Tower 8. Explore the Witch's Spooky Mansion9.Travel to and enjoy the Royal Holiday PartyVisit us at facebook.com/AlexaMagicDoor for tips, tricks, and news.
title: The Magic Door

author: by Sony Pictures Television
commands: ['"Alexa, Play Jeopardy!"', '"What is..."', '"Repeat"']
description: Did you know that every Jeopardy! category has an “extra” 6th clue? Now, you can play those clues on Alexa! With a single voice command, test your knowledge with new clues every weekday. Step up to the podium and play the same categories you saw on the latest episode! Play a wide range of categories including sports, pop culture, travel, world history and much more. Get the true Jeopardy! experience now as you respond, just like contestants on the show! Celebrate over 30 seasons of America’s Favorite Quiz Show®—enable the skill and play today! *PLEASE NOTE: If you have issues, questions or comments please email us at gamesupport@spe.sony.com. We want to hear directly from you!
title: Jeopardy!

author: by Delight Games
commands: ['"Alexa, open rogue\'s choice"']
description: You play a rogue in this choice-based text adventure set in a medieval fantasy world. With debts to pay to the underworld, you need to make a lot of coin fast! Perhaps worse, you're wanted by the King's men for desertion. Survival is your first priority, but can you thrive in the ruthless streets of Ring City? On top of this, can you discover the secret within the walls of the city... And beneath! Play the lovable scoundrel who just wants to enjoy his short time in this dimension!
title: Rogue's Choice (Beta)

author: by Elvis Wolcott
commands: ['"Alexa, ask destiny two countdown how long is left"', '"Alexa, ask destiny two countdown how long until Destiny two"', '"Alexa, ask destiny two countdown how many days until the beta"']
description: This skill helps keep you up to date on Destiny 2 news. You can get a countdown for the release or any other important dates like the beta or special events. The skill will keeps you informed about the date of all the important dates in Destiny 2 so that you are always prepared.

author: by Mobile Labs
commands: ['"Alexa, ask smart explorer to give me a tip."', '"give me a breath of the wild fact."', '"tell me a tip"']
description: You can ask for tips, tricks, and facts about the amazing Breath of the Wild video game in this unofficial Zelda skill!

author: by Avrin Ross
commands: ['"Alexa, open Game of Thrones quotes"', '"Alexa, open Game of Thrones quotes and get a new quote"', '"Alexa, ask Game of Thrones quotes to give me a quote"']
description: This skill features a realm of various quotes from Game of Thrones. Simply ask Alexa to give you a quote from Game of Thrones and it will provide you with a random quote from one of the characters in the show or a quote/motto from one of the Houses in Game of Thrones. This skill is filled with quotes from all seasons so far. Enjoy! Winter is Here!I made this as a fan of Game of Thrones. I'm not officially associated with Game of Thrones, George RR Martin, or HBO.(Game of Thrones is for mature audiences only, and this skill includes some mature quotes from the show.)

author: by Fluff Stuff Studios
commands: ['"Alexa, open Simple Pokedex"', '"Alexa, tell Simple Pokedex i choose Squirtle"', '"who\'s that pokemon"']
description: With Simple Pokédex, you can ask Alexa for more information about a Pokémon either by their name, or by their correct Pokédex entry number. If you're feeling really adventurous, say 'who's that Pokémon?' to be introduced to a completely random Pokémon!- Supports #1 - #721 (latest generation coming)- Extremely simple to useGotta Catch 'Em All!

author: by Azalea Labs
commands: ['"Alexa, start Animal Game"', '"Alexa, play Animal Game"']
description: Test Alexa’s animal knowledge by having her guess an animal of your choice. Alexa will ask you questions to figure out your chosen animal, so make sure you’re familiar with the basics! What color is it? Can it fly? Does it live in hot climates? Your answers to these questions will help Alexa narrow down the animal possibilities and make the best guess. Will you be able to stump Alexa, or will she be victorious in the end?  Alexa knows over three hundred animals and can also tell you some interesting facts about them. Did you know that rats laugh when they are tickled? And that no polar bear has ever met a penguin?
title: Animal Game

author: by Midha
commands: ['"Alexa, ask baby groot when is the next Guardians of the Galaxy movie coming..."', '"Alexa, ask baby groot what is the next guardians adventure?"', '"Alexa, ask baby groot to tell me a fact"']
description: This is a special skill of one of your favorite Marvel characters: Groot!It can reply back to you in its own unique way. Try it out.Try :Alexa, ask baby groot when is the next Guardians of the Galaxy movie coming?Alexa, ask baby groot to tell me a factAlexa, ask baby groot to tell somethingAlexa, ask baby groot to tell anything

author: by Voice Apps, LLC.
commands: ['"Alexa, open Millionaire Game"', '"Alexa, play Millionaire Game"', '"Alexa, start Millionaire Game"']
description: Millionaire Quiz Game is an exciting game in which the more questions you answer, the more money you win. Do you have what it takes to be the next Millionaire?HOW TO PLAY:You'll be asked a series of 14 questions. With each question, you'll be given four possible answers and will be asked to choose the correct one. If you get it right, you'll win money and move to the next question worth even more money. If you get all 14 questions correct, you'll win $1,000,000.If you get into trouble, you can use up to three lifelines. 50/50 will remove two of the wrong answers leaving you with the correct answer and one wrong answer. You can ask the question on social media and find out what others think the answer is. You can also phone one of your friends and have them help you answer the question.With over 2500 questions and more being added each week, Millionaire Quiz Game will bring you and your family hours and hours of fun! GETTING STARTED:Just say "Alexa, start Millionaire Game" to get started!DISCLAIMER:This game is for entertainment only. No real money is won or lost.FEEDBACK:We hope you'll love Millionaire Quiz Game and give us a 5-star rating. If you feel that Millionaire Quiz Game deserves less than a 5-star rating, please let us know at millionairegame@voiceapps.io and we'll do everything in our power to make it better.CONTACT US:We'd love to hear from you! If you have questions, comments, or feedback, please e-mail us at millionairegame@voiceapps.io.
title: Millionaire Quiz Game

author: by Brendan Cain
commands: ['"Alexa Open Zombie Hunter"']
description: This is an indoor zombie hunting game for Adults. You will need some kind of Nerf or foam dart gun. This skill will read off locations in your home, and the player will need to shoot that spot before the time runs out. Happy Hunting!

author: by Magoosh
commands: ['"Alexa Start Vocabulary Builder"', '"Alexa Launch Vocabulary Builder"', '"Alexa Open Vocabulary Builder"']
description: Vocabulary Builder is verbal adaptation of Magoosh's vocabulary builder flashcard game on both Android and iOS.Once you've enabled the skill, say "Alexa, launch Vocabulary Builder".Alexa will play a five-question game with you. It works like this:Alexa picks a random question from our list of vocabulary words, such as, "Which of the following is a synonym of laborious? (knowledgable, skilled, demanding)"If you respond with the correct answer, you score 1 point. If you don't, Alexa will tell you what the correct answer is and move onto the next question. See if you can answer all five correctly!You can use this skill as a quick daily exercise to study advanced vocabulary. Please rate and review this skill if you enjoyed it, and let us know how to improve the skill to fit your vocabulary building needs!If you are interested in finding other educational or test prep materials, please search Magoosh on the App Store or Google Play Store. Enjoy!
title: Magoosh Vocabulary Builder

author: by Matt Mitchell
commands: ['"Alexa, ask Grumpy GM to taunt Matt."', '"Alexa, tell Grumpy GM to please taunt Sarah"', '"Alexa, tell Grumpy GM to please give me a taunt for Bob"']

With often-updated phrases, this fun little game accessory will add many laughs to your game nights!Coming soon, ask Alexa to roll dice, pick a random number or flip a coin!

commands: ['"Alexa, ask question of the day."', '"Alexa, play question of the day."', '"Alexa, play the game question of the day."']
description: Every day, Question of the Day poses a new trivia question for you to respond to, from arts and entertainment to literature and science. Question of the Day is a great way to both test and improve your cultural literacy. Collect points and hear how others have answered.

author: by Seth Tenembaum
commands: ['"Alexa, get the current maps from the squid sisters."', '"Alexa, ask the squid sisters what ranked mode is on?"', '"Alexa, ask the squid sisters what are the next turf war stages?"']
description: Want to know what turf wars and ranked maps are on before booting up your Wii U? Ask Alexa and enjoy playing Splatoon!Please note this is a fan-made project, unofficial and not sponsored or endorsed by Nintendo.You can ask for the current maps or the next maps. You can specify if you're only interested in the turf wars ranked maps specifically. For example: "Alexa, ask the squid sisters what are the current ranked maps?" You can ask specifically what the ranked mode is, and finally you can ask when this rotation will end.Below lists an example for each intent.Alexa, ask the squid sisters what stages are onAlexa, ask the squid sisters what ranked stages are onAlexa, ask the squid sisters what turf war stages are onAlexa, ask the squid sisters what ranked mode is onAlexa, ask the squid sisters what stages are on nextAlexa, ask the squid sisters what ranked stages are on nextAlexa, ask the squid sisters what turf war stages are on nextAlexa, ask the squid sisters what ranked mode is on nextAlexa, ask the squid sisters when will this rotation end

commands: ['"Alexa, open Sorting Game"', '"Start the game"', '"Number two"']

author: by Warner Bros
commands: ['"Alexa, open the Wayne Investigation"', '"Visit crime lab"', '"Chase thief"']
description: Who killed Thomas and Martha Wayne? In this mystery game, Alexa guides you as you hit the mean streets of Gotham to investigate the murder of young Bruce Wayne’s parents. Can you navigate around the story’s dead ends to find the path that solves the crime? To launch this skill, say “Open the Wayne Investigation.” During the game, you can say "repeat options," "go back," or "skip." For further assistance, say "help".Parental guidance suggested. The Wayne Investigation contains content that may not suitable for all ages.
title: The Wayne Investigation

author: by Iron Raptor Digital
commands: ['"Alexa, open craft helper"', '"Alexa, ask craft helper how to craft a diamond sword"', '"Alexa, ask craft helper how do I breed horses"']
description: Craft Helper is an unofficial Minecraft assistant that helps you find information without having to browse or search for it. Simply ask it your question based on the examples below and it will do it’s best to find that information for you. If there is any information missing or should be added please let us know. We are constantly adding synonyms for crafting items.Here are a some examples of commands you can say (start with "Alexa, ask craft helper..."):Build“... build end portal”“... how do I build a snowman”“... how do I build an iron golem”“... how do I build nether portal”Breed“... breed horses”“... how do you breed pigs”“... how do I breed a cow”“... how to breed two sheep”Craft“... craft bed”“... how do you craft a diamond sword”“... how do I craft cookies”“... how to craft a furnace”Random“... random”“... tell me a random recipe”“... what is a random recipe”“... give me a random recipe”Smelt“... smelt oak wood”“... what happens when I smelt iron ingot”“... what does smelting cactus produce”“... how do I smelt iron ore”Tame“... tame ocelot”“... how do you tame horses”“... how do I tame a parrot”“... how to tame wolves”Change LogAugust 27, 2017- Red flower, yellow flower, and double plant data values now translate.- If you don’t say an item to smelt, you will be suggested a random one.- If you don’t say something to build, you will be suggested a random one.- Random will now include smelting recipes and building information.August 20, 2017- Quicker intents added to the examples above.- If you don’t say an item to craft, you will be suggested a random one.- Crafting will check building and then smelting if the previous recipe is not found.- Building will check crafting and then smelting if the previous recipe is not found.- Smelting will check crafting and then building if the previous recipe is not found.August 5, 2017- Added UK language support.- Asking about building will check crafting.- You can now ask alexa to repeat what was just said.- Smelting recipes added.- If crafting recipe not found, it will check smelting.July 25, 2017- Updated skill to use slot synonyms.- Wired up items.json file which will hold brewing, smelting, crafting recipes, where items are found, and how items are used.- Restructured files and separated out repeated code into helpers.- Misc fixes for items like villager breeding info and log type references. July 16, 2017- Updated the way rows and columns are referenced.- Added what materials and quantity you need before the recipe is read.- Added an ask emit so you don’t have to say “ask craft helper blah blah blah” each time.- Added random intent so you can just hear a random recipe.- Allowed this skill to be used in all countries but still restricted to en-US language.If you have any suggestions or comments send me an email at khanjal@gmail.com.Recipes provided by: MinecraftData (https://github.com/FVbico/MinecraftData) * Not affiliated with Mojang or Microsoft.
title: Craft Helper - Unofficial Minecraft Assistant

author: by LC Publishing
commands: ['"Alexa, ask random facts to tell me a fact."', '"Alexa, ask random facts to give me a fact."', '"Alexa, ask random facts to tell me a random fact."']

author: by Tellables
commands: ['"Alexa, start tricky genie"', '"Alexa, launch tricky genie"', '"Alexa, ask tricky genie for a story"']
description: Think you can outsmart the tricky genie? Try this game that’s suitable for all ages. Alexa will tell you a quick story about one or more characters that get themselves into a difficult predicament. The tricky genie will appear holding three sacks. One sack contains the very best solution to the problem. The genie will only give you two chances to pick the sack with the best solution. But the genie may try to trick you into being satisfied with a solution that isn't the best one. After each game, you can choose to have Alexa ask you two questions about the story to train your listening comprehension skills.This game is brought to you by the team at Tellables. Visit us at Tellables.com to learn about our other skills and to get updates on Tricky Genie.
title: Tricky Genie

By default you answer 5 questions per game session, but this can be changed.More questions will be added in the future.Icon credits to: https://www.flickr.com/photos/tarale/4444415690

commands: ['"Alexa, ask insta lock who should I insta lock?"', '"Tell me a champ to play."', '"Give me a random champion."']
description: By asking Alexa phrases such as "give me a champ" or "who should I instalock", you can find a whole new way to decide who to bring to Summoner's Rift. This will allow you to cut down on precious seconds to build out your mastery page for your instalock champ or flame your team for not allowing you your main role. Either way, a win-win for you. Enjoy and GLHF!

author: by Alexander King
commands: ['"Alexa, tell my Pet Rock to eat something"', '"Alexa, ask my Pet Rock to go play"', '"Alexa, ask my Pet Rock for an update"']
description: Take care of your own pet rock. Take your new pet on walks, play games with it, and feed it regularly, so that it grows big and strong! Your pet will grow up over time to learn more skills and tricks. Compare your rock with others to see how it stacks up!HOW TO PLAY:You start the game by picking up a shiny new rock. You can choose its color and give your rock its own name. Your rock needs to be fed regularly so that it doesn't go hungry. You can tell it to 'eat something' and it will do as you say. In addition to needing to eat, your rock also needs exercise. Make sure it plays games daily, otherwise it will get too hyper. Your rock gets full after eating too much and gets tired of playing, but it always is willing to do tricks or go for a walk.Even though rocks are simple creatures, they make great pets! Take care of your rock over time and it will grow up big and strong.TIPS:* You can change your rocks name or color anytime.* Ask your rock for an update to see its stats and how it compares to others.* Not all activities tire out your rock. There are some thing it can do all day long!* Ask your rock what trick it knows to see what it can do. The more it grows, the more tricks it will learn!* See your Alexa app for details when you ask your pet rock how it is doing.FEEDBACK:If you love this skill, please leave a 5-star review! If for any reason you don't think it deserves 5 stars, please email me your feedback alex@gotalex.com. I am also open to new ideas to make the experience better!
title: My Pet Rock

commands: ['"Alexa, open Star Wars Quotes"', '"Alexa, ask Star Wars Quotes for a quote"', '"Alexa, give me a quote from Star Wars Quotes"']
description: Everyone likes Star Wars, right? Why not get an awesome Star Wars quote every once in a while? Star Wars Quotes does what it says on the metaphorical box: Gives you Star Wars Quotes!I made this as a Star Wars fan, and I am not associated with Star Wars, Lucasfilm, or Disney in any way.May the force be with you.
title: Star Wars Quotes

author: by Justin Bui
commands: ['"Alexa, open super smash game"', '"Yes"', '"Start Over Please"']
description: An Interaction between you and Alexa! Welcome to Name that Smash Character! Alexa will then ask you a series of questions, and from these questions alone, Alexa will figure out the character you chose!

commands: ['"Alexa, start haunted adventure"', '"Alexa, open haunted adventure"', '"Alexa, begin haunted adventure"']

author: by Majel Tech
commands: ['"Alexa, talk to poke evolve."', '"Alexa, ask poke evolve about Magikarp."', '"Alexa, ask poke evolve to repeat that."']
description: PokEvolve allows you to look up the evolution info for various Pokémon in Pokémon GO. Just ask about a Pokémon form, and it will tell you about the evolution chain and how many candies are required to evolve to the next form.For example, say "Alexa, ask poke evolve about Magikarp", and it will tell you that 400 candies are required to evolve Magikarp into Gyarados.You can also say "Ask poke evolve about the skill itself", or, if you miss a response, you can say "Ask poke evolve to repeat that".At Majel Tech, we pride ourselves on our best-in-class language recognition and pronunciation. We've spent a lot of time at thinking up anything you might naturally say in requesting PokEvolve's functionality. Go ahead, try it! We think you'll be pleased.Note: that being said, we're not perfect! Sometimes PokEvolve might not give you exactly what you asked for. Please try again, and if it doesn't work, let us know! We want to continually improve our language recognition and pronunciation, and your feedback helps us do that! You can use the "Send Feedback" link at the bottom of this screen, or on our Facebook page, https://www.facebook.com/MajelTech/ to do so. Thanks!PokEvolve for Pokemon GO is an unofficial skill and is not affiliated with or endorsed by Nintendo.
title: PokEvolve for Pokemon GO

author: by Kissell
commands: ['"Alexa, ask Issac for the Daily Missions"', '"Alexa, ask Issac to describe the talent Reckless"', '"Alexa, ask Issac about the skill Support Station"']
description: With this skill you can get information for The Division video game. At the time of releasing this skill there were 83 gear/weapon/ability talents in the game, and skill can describe them all to you. It can also tell you what talents can be rolled on a piece of gear, and what the daily missions are.Some really common phrases you could use would be things like the following:Alexa, ask Issac how long until resetAlexa, ask Issac for the Daily Missions NOTE: Daily Missions are scraped from Reddit Posts which are done manually by a moderator, so information may take some time after daily reset.Alexa, ask Issac what talents can I roll on <Knee Pads>  NOTE: (change Knee Pads to other types of gear)Alexa, ask Issac to about the skill <Support Station> NOTE: (change Support Station to any skill)Alexa, ask Issac to about the talent <Vigorous> NOTE: (change Vigorous to any talent)Alexa, ask Issac about <Jessica Kandel> NOTE: (You can use any main story character's name here)Alexa, ask Issac about <Cleaners> NOTE: (most of the common jargon in game is defined here, adding more all the time)
title: Issac for The Division

author: by Fangtastico
commands: ['"Alexa, start dungeon adventure"', '"Alexa, open dungeon adventure"', '"Alexa, begin dungeon adventure"']
description: Ravensburg needs your help, an evil necromancer and his monsters have been coming from the dungeon and attacking the town. Your task is to locate the evil necromancer who is somewhere in the dungeon and slay him to save the town. In this dungeon crawling game you will create a character and purchase items from the town such as weapons, armor, potions and spells but beware because the dungeon contains many different types of monsters and traps.This is a complete fantasy role-playing game in which Alexa will become the dungeon master. You will create a character, purchase and sell items in the town, travel to the dungeon, fight monsters, cast spells, drink potions, level up your character, find chests, get more gold to go back to town and purchase better items. First you will create a character and assign values to your character's attributes of strength, dexterity, intelligence, constitution, perception, charisma and wisdom. The adventure will involve rolling dice to determine the outcomes of various tasks (Alexa will roll the dice for you). Your character's attributes will affect how well your character does during the adventure giving you bonus modifiers that add or subtract from your rolls. You will encounter various types of monsters in the dungeon that you can attack and kill which will give your character experience points that will be used to level up your character.Alexa will save your character and your dungeon state for you so that you can continue from where you left off (even if you are in the middle of fighting a monster). Dungeon Adventure is a game meant to be played over many sessions and if you die you can always come back and try again with a new character and dungeon environment (and maybe try a different strategy).It will be a difficult task to find the evil necromancer and slay him but if you do it you will go down in the dungeon adventure HALL OF FAME. For news and tips join us on Facebook under Alexa Dungeon Adventure: https://www.facebook.com/AlexaDungeonAdventureSome of the useful things you can say:WHERE AM I / LOOK AROUNDGO / MOVE / TRAVEL / RUN / EVADE (north, west, east, south, etc)RESTTALKTRAINWHAT IS MY (strength, dexterity, intelligence, armor class, level, etc)HOW MANY (hit points, experience points, etc) DO I HAVEHOW MUCH (gold, etc) DO I HAVEWHAT IS MY CURRENT STATUSWHAT EFFECTS ARE ON MEWHAT AM I CURRENTLY AFFECTED BYWHAT (weapons, armors, potions, spells, etc) DO I HAVELIST MY (weapons, armors, potions, spells, items)EXAMINE (item name)EQUIP / READY / PULL OUT (weapon name)WHAT WEAPON AM I USINGWEAR / CHANGE INTO (armor name)WHAT ARMOR AM I WEARINGLIST (weapons, armors, potions, spells) FOR SALEPURCHASE (item name)SELL (item name)WHAT WAS I OFFERED FOR MY (item name)ATTACK HIGH, MIDDLE, LOWDEFEND HIGH, MIDDLE, LOWHOW MANY HIT POINTS DOES THE (monster) HAVE LEFTDRINK POTION OF (potion name)CAST (spell name) SPELLEXAMINE CHEST FOR TRAPSDISARM CHEST TRAPPICK CHEST LOCKPRY CHEST LOCKOPEN CHESTEXAMINE FOUNTAINMONSTER INFO / MONSTER STATSCALL ME (character name)WHAT IS MY CHARACTER'S NAMELISTENASK FOR DIVINE ASSISTANCE / PRAYGAME STATSWHO IS IN THE HALL OF FAMEINVENTORYCHARACTER SHEET / CHARACTER STATSHelpful Tips:- Have some healing potions to drink- Go back to town after you've acquired more gold to purchase better weapons, armor, potions and spells- Keep track of your current hit points (you can always ask "How many hit points do I have?")- Kill monsters to gain experience points to level up your character (you can always ask "How many experience points do I have?")- You can drink potions, cast spells, run, open chests, etc even in combat if it is your turn- Use MONSTER INFO to help determine how powerful the monster is by getting its stats- Sometimes it is better to try to run from a monster than continue fighting- You can always relaunch dungeon adventure and pick up where you left the game
title: Dungeon Adventure

author: by Mark Mattione
commands: ['"Alexa, tell Lord Vader there is a great disturbance in the Force."', '"Alexa, tell Lord Vader that Com Scan has detected an energy field protectin..."', '"Alexa, tell Lord Vader that I will never join him."']
description: Have a conversation with Lord Vader! You can "Tell Lord Vader" a variety of quotes from the movies and Alexa will respond in kind with Vader's lines. If you love to quote Star Wars then you will love this skill.For the moment, only quotes from the Empire Strikes Back are supported. Try: You: Alexa, tell Lord Vader Com Scan has detected an energy field protecting an area of the sixth planet of the Hoth System. The field is strong enough to deflect any bombardment.  Lord Vader: ... You: He... felt surprise was wiser...  Lord Vader: ...  You: Yes, my Lord. You: Alexa, tell Lord Vader the fleet has moved out of lightspeed and we're preparing to... [stop, and suddenly begin to choke, clutching at your throat]  Lord Vader: ... Your friend: Yes, my lord?  Lord Vader: ...  You: [utter one last strangled gasp, and fall over]  Your friend: Thank you, Lord Vader. You: Alexa, tell Lord Vader our ships have sighted the Millennium Falcon. But it has entered an asteroid field and we can not risk... You: Alexa, tell Lord Vader that the Emperor commands you to make contact with him. Lord Vader: ... You: there is a great disturbance in the Force.  Lord Vader: ... You: We have a new enemy. Luke Skywalker. Lord Vader: ... You: He could destroy us.  Lord Vader: ...  You: The Force is strong with him. The son of Skywalker must not become a Jedi.  Lord Vader: ...  You: [intrigued] Yes... He would be a great asset. Can it be done?  Lord Vader: He will join us or die, master.  You: Alexa, ask Lord Vader about Leia and the Wookiee Lord Vader: ...  You: [outraged] That was never a condition of our agreement, nor was giving Han to this bounty hunter!  Lord Vader: ... You: [after a pause; nervous tone] No.  Lord Vader: ... You: [to yourself] This deal is getting worse all the time! You: Alexa, tell Lord Vader I'll never join him!  Lord Vader: ... You: He told me enough! He told me *you* killed him!  Lord Vader: ... You: No. That's not true. That's impossible!  Lord Vader: ... You: [anguished] No! No!This skill is fan-created and has no affiliation with Disney or Lucasfilm.

author: by Invoked Apps LLC
commands: ['"Alexa, play Deal or No Deal"', '"Alexa, open Deal or No Deal"', '"Alexa, start Deal or No Deal"']
description: Can you find the case containing $1,000,000 or trick the Banker into giving you more money than your case is worth?HOW TO PLAY:The game begins by selecting 1 of 20 cases, each containing a hidden amount of money ranging from $.01 to $1,000,000. The case you chose stays by your side throughout the remainder of the game, and you begin to open the remaining cases in a series of rounds to reveal the amount of money inside them. At the end of each round Alexa will receive a phone call from "The Banker" who will offer you a sum of money to quit the game and forfeit your case. If you think your case contains more than the Banker's offer, you turn down the deal and continue playing the game. If you think your case is worth less than the Banker's offer, you accept the deal, the game ends, and your case is revealed to see if you made the right choice. The Banker's offers will change throughout the game based on the likelihood of your case containing a large or small amount of money.Your goal is to out-smart the Banker and finish the game with the greatest amount of money possible, so consider the offers wisely!TIPS:- You can say "random" to pick an available case at random instead of keeping track of the case numbers.- Not sure which cases are available? You can say “what cases are left?” for a list.- Open the Alexa app while opening cases to see which cases are available to pick from.- Open the Alexa app during a Banker offer to see which cash amounts are still in play.FEEDBACK:If you love this Skill, please leave a 5-star review! If for any reason you don't think it deserves 5 stars, please email me with your feedback at alexaskills@nickschwab.com.DISCLAIMER:No real money is won or lost by playing this game.
title: Deal or No Deal Game (unofficial)

author: by Verto Lab
commands: ['"Alexa, open Categories Game"', '"Alexa, play Categories Game"', '"Alexa, ask Categories Game to play"']
description: Categories Game is a fast-paced word game. In this game, you will be presented with different categories and asked to come up with a word that begins with a certain letter in each category. Stimulate your grey matter in this engaging game!NEW: Unlock categories by playing more rounds. Alexa will tell you at the end of the round when does a new category unlocks!HOW TO PLAY:Alexa: "I rolled the letter A. First category is Animal..."You: "Animal, Ant"Alexa: "Ant is correct. Great. Next category is Country"You: "Country, Austria"Alexa: "Austria, nice answer. Next up is..."And so on...If you enjoyed playing Scrabble™ or Scattergories™, you will have tons of fun with Categories Game!** Categories Game may sometimes have trouble getting the word correctly or let you say a word that doesn't belong in the category, but we are constantly expanding the lexicon and the game keeps improving with time. Thanks for your understanding.FEEDBACK:If you like the game, please leave a review. If something is wrong or you've had a bad experience, please write us before leaving a negative review at feedback@categories-game.com, thank you!LEADERBOARD:Do your quickest and sharpest to get on the leaderboard.- See the scoring system below.- Find the leaderboard at http://www.categories-game.comSCORE: - If you could not answer on time, had a wrong answer or Alexa had trouble understanding you (we're sorry for that), you get 0 points for the category. - If your answer was accepted, you get 50 minus the number of seconds it took you to answer.- Your score is the sum of points you received in a round.TIPS:- You can skip a category by saying "Skip category" or "I don't know". If you don't say anything for longer than 6 seconds the game will quit (Alexa's interface limitation).- You can say "repeat category" if you've lost track or need to buy some time to think.- If Alexa rolled the same letter twice or you just want to change the letter for any reason, say "Change the letter".- Try maximizing your score by acing all categories without mistakes!

author: by Business After Dark
commands: ['"Alexa, open Scope Skills"', '"new target"', '"ready"']
description: This skill allows you to practice your ability to range targets from a submarine's periscope. Pursuing your dolphins or prepping for SOAC? Check out this skill!Given a target's masthead height and the number of high-powered divisions, you will be asked for its range. Remember, the ranging equation is: Range = (80 * Masthead Height) / (# of High-Powered Divisions). When finished, give the order to proceed deep!Simply ask Alexa to open Scope Skills, say you are ready, and practice away! Good luck!(Skill image by Hayden Kerrisk)

author: by James Church
commands: ['"Alexa, launch Yeti Hunt Game"', '"begin game"', '"move north"']
description: Hunt the Yeti (or Yeti Hunt) is an interpretation of the game Hunt The Wumpus (1972). In this game, you guide a hunter through a dark cave to discover the location of the yeti. Once you have helped the hunter locate the yeti, tell the hunter to throw the hunter's only spear in the direction of the yeti. If you are right about the location, you will help the hunter defeat the yeti! If not, the yeti will eventually find the hunter.In this version of the game, the hunter is lost in a 5 by 5 cave. There are open pits, bats, and a single yeti. You hear the bats flutter, feel the breeze from the open pit, or smell the yeti near by. Bats will pick the hunter up and drop the hunter in a random (safe) location. If the hunter falls into a pit, the hunter dies and the game is over. If the hunter walks into the yeti, the yeti attacks and the hunter dies. Only the hunter is capable of moving, but the hunter only has one spear, so make it count!Game features:- "begin game": Starts a new game.- "how to play": Reminds the player how to play.- "overview": Provides a short overview of Hunt the Yeti.- "pause": Provides a short prompt and allows the player to think.Once you are playing the game, there are two actions to remember:- "move [direction]": Moves the hunter in a particular direction.- "throw [direction]": Throws the spear in a particular direction.A direction is always north, south, east, or west. The game will guide you about where open rooms are, but it won't tell you what are in those rooms. It's up to you to use deductive reasoning to figure out where the Yeti and other traps are located. Good luck!You may also say a direction and the hunter will automatically move in that direction. (For some reason, I have trouble moving the hunter "south". Maybe it's an issue with my accent. For that case, I say "move south".)Full source code and acknowledgements are on the game's GitHub page:https://github.com/jcchurch/HuntTheYetiAlexa
title: Hunt the Yeti

description: The Ultimate Pokédex (U Dex) is your best companion in the wonderful world of Pokémon. This skill will help you identify useful type matchups, learn the matchups you don't already know (there are quizzes and tips), search the Ultimate Pokédex by name and number, and much, much more. Best of all, every response is custom tailored to the game that you're currently playing.Check out the website for a detailed overview of functionality:http://ultimatepokedex.com/overview/The current list of features is already fantastic, but we are also planning many more features for the future: some trivial (how tall is Rattata?) and some extremely useful (where can i find Flabébé?). Our vision is that you should be able to use the Ultimate Pokédex as your one and only Pokémon reference, without ever having to put down your game. You can follow along with our progress here:http://blog.ultimatepokedex.com/Have a suggestion for making the Ultimate Pokédex better? Encountered a problem with one of the responses? We want to know! Feel free to contact us:http://support.ultimatepokedex.com/or support@ultimatepokedex.comWe hope you enjoy the Ultimate Pokédex. We hope you find it useful. But most of all, we hope it helps you become the very best!-----------------------------Ultimate Pokedéx is developed by GameTools ™ and is not affiliated with Nintendo, Creatures Inc., or GAME FREAK inc. Pokémon and Pokédex are properties of their respective owners.

To play: You start trapped in the middle of a square maze. You must get to the exit in the upper left or lower right corner to escape! You can choose a preset maze size small (seven square), medium (nine square), or large (eleven square.)Or, for a real challenge, you can choose a maze size from thirteen all the way up to ninety-nine! description: Engage in classic fantasy adventure. Build a team of up to six companions to explore exotic cities, high castles, and deep dungeons. Some of the more used commands are:North, South, East, West: move around the game map.Enter: enter into a town, castle or dungeon.inventory: list what your party and your active player is carryingwho: list the companions in your groupactivate <name>: make one of your companions the active companiongive <item> to <name>: give an item from the party inventory to the companiontake <item> from <name>: move an item from a companion to the party inventory When in combat you cannot use the move commands. However you can:fight: fight a round of combat with the enemyrun away: flee a fightFor a demo of the skill, see this video: https://youtu.be/KToMLNCZ8ZIFor questions, technical support, or to talk to other players, please join the discussion board here: http://starlanes.freeforums.net/board/5/6-swords-discussion

You can place several different types of bets - both interior (single number, split between two numbers, on the corner of four adjacent numbers, on a row covering 3 or 6 numbers, or on a column of 12 numbers) and exterior (red, black, high, low, even, odd, or on one of the dozens).Keep track of your high score, separately per wheel, and compare how you're doing with other players by saying "read high scores" to hear the leader board. Keep playing and you can move to the top!We also feature an exciting tournament round every Thursday. author: by Game Construct
commands: ['"Alexa, tell Dice Bag to roll for me"', '"Alexa, ask Dice Bag who goes first"', '"Alexa, tell Dice Bag to roll for percent"']
description: Dice Bag rolls a number of multi-sided dice. You can use Dice Bag as a dice replacement or companion for your rolling needs.Just Roll: Roll the standard 6 sided dice by saying "roll my dice" to automatically roll two 6 sided dice. Example: "Alexa, ask Dice Bag to roll my dice."Roll Multi-sided: Roll a number of multi-sided dice. An example command would be "roll 7 d 20" or "roll 7 twenty sided dice" to roll 7 twenty sided dice. The maximum number of dice to roll at one time is 100. Example: "Alexa, ask Dice Bag to roll seven d twenty."Last Roll: Forget your last roll? Ask Dice Bag "what was the last roll?" Example: "Alexa, ask Dice Bag what was my last roll?"Re-Roll: To re-roll the last set of dice, just say "re-roll" or "roll again." Example: "Alexa, as Dice Bag to roll again."See Who Goes First: Dice Bag can also help determine the first player, as is common in many board games. Simply ask Dice Bag "who goes first." Then tell Dice Bag the number of players. The maximum number of players who can roll for first player at one time is 15. Example: "Alexa, ask Dice Bag to see who goes first."Roll Initiative: For specialized gaming needs, initiative has been added to help players determine the order of character actions during encounters. Say "roll for initiative," then tell Dice Bag the number of players. The specified number of d20 will be rolled. The maximum number of players who can roll for initiative at one time is 15. Example: "Alexa, ask Dice Bag to roll for initiative."Roll Percent: Dice Bag can also roll percent dice. Just say "roll for percent." Example: "Alexa, ask Dice Bag to roll for percent."Dice Bag will voice up to 15 dice results at a time, otherwise just the total is voiced. You can view up to 50 roll results in the Alexa App.To get basic instructions, say "Alexa, open Dice Bag."
title: Dice Bag

author: by DaysFly
commands: ['"Alexa, play Escape Room."', '"What can I do?"', '"Alexa, ask Escape Room to find a real life escape room near me."']
description: Escape Room is an interactive role-playing adventure. You get to choose one of two different escape rooms. The goal is to solve the puzzles and find your way out, using only your words and your wits. You will be interacting with characters that you meet, picking up items, reading clues, searching for secrets, and avoiding deadly traps as you try to escape. Unlike a real-life escape room, you aren't on a timer. And magic sometimes works, depending on the kind of world you enter. Each escape room is its own mini-world. Each contains a unique way to get hints, if you get stuck.Merlin's Cave: This escape room finds you trapped within the wizard's quarters, surrounded by magical items and potions as you try to find the wizard himself. It turns out he's been missing for centuries, but you must locate him and get his help to escape. Difficulty: Medium.The Tomb of the Lost Pharaoh: You're that famous raider of tombs, you know who. Yes, that one. This time, you got yourself trapped in an ancient tomb, hidden for centuries by some unknown power. With the entrance blocked by fallen rubble, you have to locate and save your partner, Owen, who is the only one who knows the other way out. Just be aware that your presence is known and felt by some ancient evil, and escaping its clutches won't be easy. Difficulty: Medium.If you live in the United States or Canada, you can also ask Alexa to find a REAL LIFE ESCAPE ROOM near you! She will offer you her top picks for a live adventure, and send location and contact information to your Alexa app.More escape rooms are on the way! These two are just the beginning. Join our mailing list at https://daysfly.com to be notified when new adventures appear.Put on your thinking cap and let the adventure begin. If you find yourself struggling and need a hint, contact us through our contact page.For information about our other games, or for a list of all the things you can do and say in these adventures, visit our web site, https://daysfly.com.
title: Escape Room

author: by Amazon
commands: ['"Alexa, open Cleo."', '"French."', '"Alexa, ask Cleo how I\'m doing."']
description: You love learning new things from Alexa and now it’s your turn to help her learn! Do you speak a language that Alexa doesn’t understand? Cleo is your opportunity to share more about that language and culture with Alexa. You’ll be prompted by Alexa in English to respond to her in your chosen language or dialect. Earn points, level up, and help contribute to Alexa’s future understanding.Getting started:1. Say “Alexa, open Cleo.” (Pronounced: KLEE-oh)2. Alexa will describe how the skill works and ask you for the language you speak. Say the name of your language in English (e.g. French, Mandarin, Hindi). 3. Alexa will ask you to confirm the language and will move into the first learning round.4. During each round, Alexa will ask you to say five things in your language. Wait for her to prompt you and then go ahead and respond in the language you specified. She may ask you to say something specific or to just say anything at all. The type of round will differ each time you play.5. Aim to speak as naturally as possible in your language. It’s better to say something naturally then to translate. 6. To close Cleo during a learning round, just say “Alexa, exit.”7. Want a summary for how much you’ve contributed so far? Just say, “Alexa, ask Cleo how I’m doing.”You accumulate points for each phrase and can level up throughout the week. You earn bonus points for each consecutive day you play in a single week. See if you can reach Diamond level before the next Monday (UTC time). Sample Interaction:User: Alexa open Cleo.Alexa: Welcome back! Would you like to continue teaching me French?User: Yes.Alexa: OK, think of a city where they speak French. Ask me for the weather there.User: Quel temps fait-il à Toulouse?Alexa: Ask me for the time.User: Quelle heure est-il?Alexa: Think of your favorite French song. Ask me to play it.User: Joue La Vie en Rose par Edith Piaf.Alexa: Think of an actor. Ask me when they were born.User: Quand est-ce que Jean Dujardin est né?Alexa: Think of a store where you shop. Ask me when it opens.User: À quelle heure est-ce que Carrefour ouvre?Alexa: Thanks! Would you like to do another round?User: Yes!*Cleo was developed by a team of linguists and data scientists who share a passion for languages and dialects from around the world. If you experience issues using the skill or would like to share feedback, please submit feedback through the Alexa app.Levels:Bronze: 50 pointsSilver: 100 pointsGold: 200 pointsPlatinum: 500 pointsDiamond: 1000 pointsDaily Bonus:1st day: 02nd day: 53rd day: 104th day: 205th day: 506th day: 1007th day: 200
title: Cleo

author: by Nibroc Productions
commands: ['"Alexa, open Shut The Box"', '"Roll the Dice"', '"Shut the 9"']
description: It's the traditional pub game Shut the Box now available to play with Alexa! Try to shut all the boxes and get the lowest score possible!The object of the game is to try to close all of the boxes numbered 1 through 9. You play a solo game each time. Each turn, you'll roll the dice and then pick boxes one at a time to shut. For example, let's say you roll a 12. You could shut the 9 box which would leave you with 3 of your roll remaining. You could choose the 1 box and the 2 box to close or you could choose the 3 box to close. Once you're done closing boxes for that rolll, you'll roll again. As long as your total roll can be used to close remaining boxes, you'll keep rolling and shutting boxes. If you're not sure what boxes are left open (or closed), ask Alexa for the status of the game and she'll let you know. You can also open the Alexa smartphone app and follow along with what boxes are opened on there.
title: Shut the Box

author: by Drawrz.com
commands: ['"Alexa, open music teacher"', '"Alexa, ask music teacher to Teach Me a Lesson"', '"Alexa, ask music teacher to Teach Me Twinkle Twinkle Little Star"']
description: Are you interested in learning how to play the piano? This skill will build up the skills for any novice looking to get started.Level 1 - Free Music Lessons!Say "Teach Me a Music Lesson" and your Alexa will walk you through basics of hand position, and how to get started playing the musical scale.Level 2 - Basic Note RecognitionSay "Start Beginner Note Drill" and you can then get your hands set, then practice hearing individual notes, and trying to find them on a keyboard. This is the first step towards understanding music.Level 3 - Learn your first SongOnce you understand the notes, start with a basic song. Say "Teach Me Twinkle Twinkle Little Star" and the skill will walk through each note required to play.Level 4 - Play a Duet with AlexaOnce you have mastered the sections, see if you can play the entire song along with Alexa in a duet. Just say "Duet for Twinkle Twinkle Little Star" and see if you can keep up and play all of the notes.Music Teacher can currently teach you more than a dozen different songs. For a complete list, say "List Available Songs" and it will provide the full list.A few examples to get started (beginner level) are -- Twinkle Twinkle Little Star- Old MacDonald's Farm- Mary Had a Little Lamb- London Bridge is Falling Down- Happy BirthdayReady for the next level? Here are some with more difficulty.- Ode to Joy (Ludwig Van Beethoven)- Minuet in G (Johann Sebastian Bach)- Star Spangled Banner- Go Tell it on the Mountain- Fur Elise (Ludwig Van Beethoven)Go ahead and try it now!
title: Music Teacher

author: by Ted Battreall
commands: ['"Alexa, Launch Timeless Adventure"', '"Alexa, Open Timeless Adventure"', '"Alexa, Play Timeless Adventure"']
description: Interactive adventure game series where you travel back in time to overt disasters caused by the villainous Dr Ian Shogrin. The evil Doctor has stolen a time machine with a malicious intent to alter history. Based loosely on the television series,Timeless, this game puts you in the driver seat to fly back in time and avert catastrophes before they occur.Episode 1: Save the MayflowerDr Eli Shogrin has stolen a time machine with the intent of causing havoc on the historic Mayflower voyage. The world is relying on you to stop him. While this game is Timeless, your mission is not. Move quickly and avoid obstacles in your way to find out what dastardly deed our villain has done this time. Episode 2: Coming Soon.Group play works well with this game too! Play as a team or challenge your friends to see who can complete the game first.You move through the game by selecting a command prompted in each scene. When you encounter objects, try using action commands like "examine, take, move, open, drink, or wear. For example, "Take glasses" or "Move table". These are just some examples, try actions based on the items you see.At any time you can issue the following commands:Repeat Scene: To hear the entire scene againRepeat Options: To hear your options Go Back: To revisit the previous sceneInventory: To see what your carryingWhat Time is it?: To hear the time in the game. It may give you more than just the time if you've revealed certain things.(This requires a watch)Brief Descriptions: To provide more concise responsesVerbose Descriptions: To provide more verbose responsesHint: To get ideas of things to tryPause: To pause game play for one minute.Help: To hear these commands againStart Again: To start the game overQuit: To end the game (game will be saved)Learn More: https://fb.me/AlexaTimelessAdventure
title: Timeless Adventure

author: by Extentia Information Technology
commands: ['"Alexa, ask MyBrickBot to add set number one zero two five three in my own c..."', '"Alexa, ask MyBrickBot for sets in my wish list"', '"Alexa, ask MyBrickBot to send me instruction manual for set one zero two fi..."']
description: Attention all LEGO® lovers! Gone are the days of clamoring around the internet for information about your vintage Millennium Falcon®, of frantically scouring your house for that Architects® set that you swear you have. Rejoice, for the MyBrickBot Alexa skill is here! Our innovative skill is the ultimate reference tool for LEGO® enthusiasts around the world. Our skill is integrated with the immensely popular brickset.com database, allowing us to use their vast library of LEGO® information to enhance your experience.From our skill, you can add sets to and remove sets from your brickset.com inventory, as well as your wish list.We also provide information on every single LEGO® set and theme since 1980, allowing users of our skill to effortlessly access premium information. BrickBot allows you to elevate your LEGO® experience, and makes those nifty bricks a lot more fun!  If you want to ask MyBrickBot for something, be sure to preface your question with the phrase, "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot"- this will let MyBrickBot know that you want to talk to it! Here’s the information that MyBrickBot can provide:Add a set to your 'own' collectionSample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot to add [set number] in own collection"Remove a set from your 'own' collectionSample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot to remove [set number] from my owned sets"Add a set to your wish list Sample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot to add [set number] to my wish list"Remove a set from your wish listSample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot to remove the set [set number] from my wish list"Get an instruction manual for the setSample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot to send me instruction manual for the set [set number]"Information on LEGO® sets - Gives you a list of all available sets for any given year. In case a set is not available for a particular year, Alexa will convey that as well. – Sample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot what sets are available in [year]"More information on LEGO® sets - Gives you set name, theme name, and year the set was released. All you need to do is provide the right set number. Sample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot to give me details for the set [set number]"Information on LEGO® themes - Gives you a list of all the available themes.Sample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot what themes are available"Information on LEGO® sets - Gives you a list of all available sets in a particular theme. Sample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot what sets are available in [theme name]"Information on LEGO® sub-themes - Gives you a list of all the available sub-themes in a theme.Sample utterance: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot what subthemes are available in [theme name]"To find out other features of the skill say: "Alexa, ask MyBrickBot for help"Do not feel restricted by this list at all, there are thousands of ways to ask MyBrickBot for something!Once you open the skill, you will be prompted to enter your email and password for brickset.com. As this skill is made in conjunction with brickset.com, it is advisable to have a brickset account in order to get the best possible experience. Do not fret if you don’t have an account, you just cannot use the inventory and wish list features of the app. Happy Building! author: by Iron Raptor Digital
commands: ['"Alexa, open server list"', '"Alexa, ask server list for a random server"', '"Alexa, ask server list for a survival server"']
description: Looking for a new server for yourself or with your friends? Find a server by telling Minecraft Server List what type of server you like to play on.Features- Specify a server type you want to play on or simply say random to get any server.- Short descriptions are allowed so owners can describe their server.- Other server tags will be read to see if the server fits your preferences.- Server address is read and spelt to try to eliminate confusion.- Server is queried if server owner provides a port for it and players online are read.Example Commands (start with “Alexa, ask server list…”)- tell me a survival server- give me a pvp server- for a prison server- server with ranks- skyblockFAQHow do I add my server to the list?* Visit https://goo.gl/forms/w6N4AfjoxltMZiK03 and fill out the form to add your server. You can visit it again to update or make changes as needed.How long until my server is used in a response?* Currently this is a manual process so it may take a day or two for your server to be in the list of responses.I don’t understand the server address that is being read back.* If you can’t understand Alexa’s pronunciation of the server address, check your alexa app on your phone to see what the response is and you’ll be able to read the address.You can also visit https://alexa.amazon.com/spa/index.html#settings/dialogs to see what’s said by Alexa.I keep getting the same server for a specific tag.* We will preload the list as much as we can but some tags may only have one or only a few servers. As more people submit servers this list will grow.I tried connecting to a server but it is offline.* We keep track of servers that fail the query check and will remove as needed. If you’ve gotten the same offline server a few times across several days let us know and we’ll investigate.I want to add a tag to my server that you don’t have on the form.* We allow a freeform tag to be added in case there’s a game mode we haven’t thought of or seen. If it’s popular enough we’ll add it to the form list.My server name or address is being pronounced wrong.* If you’ve followed all the suggestions on the google form, shoot us an email (IronRaptorDigital@gmail.com) and we will run it through Alexa’s voice simulator and adjust it where necessary.Why use this skill over just browsing a website server list?* The only real advantages are the complete randomness of the results and you’re not influenced by a flashy banner. Otherwise this is just another way to find other minecraft servers out there. Why not both?Change LogAugust 31, 2017- Added tag suggestions with the help message.- Added UK language support.- Lots of intent synonyms and other ways to get a random server.- Tag suggestion when tag isn’t found and when server is read.Add/Edit your server via the following google form:https://goo.gl/forms/w6N4AfjoxltMZiK03* Not affiliated with Mojang or Microsoft.
title: Minecraft Server List (Unofficial)

author: by Jürgen Carstensen
commands: ['"Alexa, start slot machine"', '"Alexa, open slot machine"', '"Alexa, play slot machine"']
description: Slot Machine is a gambling machine with 3 reels. On each reel are 6 different symbols. If 2 symbols match, you get your bet back. With 3 identical symbols, you will win a certain amount of coins, depending on the symbol and your bet. At 3 times seven the jackpot gets paid out. On start of your 1st game, the bank will give you 100 coins that you can use with a bet of at least one coin to a maximum of 5 coins per game. After playing, your score is entered into a highscore list and you can compete with other players. Go to the casino with Alexa and try your luck. The jackpot is waiting for you to be cracked.You can always get help with "Alexa Help".You can always read the rules with "Alexa Rules".You can pause the game with "Alexa Pause" and continue playing later.You can end or cancel the game with "Alexa stop" and continue playing later.You can increase your bet by 1 coin to a maximum of 5 coins with "Alexa raise".You can use "AlexaReduce" to reduce your bet by 1 coin to a minimum of 1 coin.You can change your player name with "Alexa new name (your name)".You can ask "Alexa how many coins do I have" your point.You can read the highscore list with "Alexa highscore".With "Alexa jackpot" you can have the jackpot read to you.I would be happy if you would take the time to evaluate my game after the game.For questions, suggestions, information or general please: EinarmigerBandit@AlexaNews.de
title: Slot Machine

author: by Chris B.
commands: ['"Alexa, open category game"', '"Alexa, start category game"']
description: ## What does this app do? Category Game is a word game where you need to guess the category or theme that the words share.* The app will give you three words, you need to guess the category that they share. The categories will be fairly broad, and will be one word, such as: metals, plants, or containers. I can repeat the category words at any time during the game, simply say 'repeat the words'.## Ok, so how do I interact with Category Game? HOW TO PLAY:---* You: "Alexa, open category game"* Alexa: "Welcome...do you want to play a game?"* You: "Yes"* Alexa: "Here are your words: covey, grouse, jackdaw* You: "are these cities?"* Alexa: "cities is not it. The category starts with the letter b. Try guessing another category."* You: "repeat the words"* Alexa: "Here are the words again: covey, grouse, jackdaw. Try guessing another category"* You: "birds"* Alexa: "birds is exactly right! in only 2 guesses ...Would you like to play again?And so on...If you're very close to the target word, but not an exact match, I may also give it to you.
title: Category Game

author: by AskMaster
commands: ['"Alexa, open Tile Trek"', '"Alexa, play Tile Trek"', '"Alexa, play the game Tile Trek"']
description: TileTrek requires a unique combination of spatial, memory, and number skills to win this challenging game. Just keep track of your movements around a grid of numbered tiles- easy enough.STARTING THE GAME: To start, first specify the size (3-10) of an NxN square grid of numbered tiles and a total number of moves to make (5-10). The grid size you specify can be from 3 to 10, and the number of moves can be from 5 to 50. For example say 3 for a 3x3 grid and say 10 for 10 total moves. Now visualize the grid of tiles filled sequentially- left to right, top to bottom- with N*N integer numbers. For example a 3x3 grid contains tiles numbered sequentially from 1 to 9, and a 4x4 grid contains tiles numbered 1-16.PLAYING THE GAME: The game always starts out on tile number 1 in the upper left corner of the grid. For game play you simply alternate back and forth with Alexa moving to an adjacent tile in any valid direction (just say “UP”, “DOWN”, “LEFT”, or “RIGHT”). On each move you must stay within the NxN grid area, and a move cannot simply undo or reverse the previous move (for example if Alexa says “UP”, your next move cannot be “DOWN”). The object of the game is to correctly guess the current tile number after the specified number of moves has been made. Your score is equal to the sum of all tiles traversed, including the first one. WINNING THE GAME: After the specified number of moves has been made, you have to correctly guess the current tile number to win the game. Additionally, if you achieved a new high score, you have to guess your score to post it in the system (see High Score section). HIGH SCORE: For each grid size, a high score is permanently stored in the TileTrek system for all Alexa users to beat. To post a new high score after winning a game, you have to correctly guess your score which is simply the tally (sum) of all tiles traversed, including the first one. If you win the game with a new high score and guess it correctly, Alexa will prompt you for your initials (3 letters) so they can be posted in the system along with your high score.Example interaction:Alexa: Select grid size and # of moves [Welcome prompt – You select a 3x3 tile grid and 5 moves]You: Right [You moved RIGHT in the grid to tile #2]Alexa: Down [Alexa moved DOWN to tile #5]You: Left [You moved LEFT to tile #4]Alexa: Down [Alexa moved DOWN to tile #7]You: Right [[You moved RIGHT to tile #8]**Total number of moves completed (=5) and Alexa now prompts you for the current tile numberYou: 8 [You correctly guess the current tile number– You win!]**Your score (total tile tally) would be 1+2+5+4+7+8 = 27 points
title: Tile Trek

author: by Josep Valls-Vargas
commands: ['"Alexa, start Audio Battleship"', '"Alexa, open Audio Battleship"', '"Alexa, start a new game of Audio Battleship"']
description: Play a single player game of battleship (also called naval battle). Alexa will create a board of the classic game and you will take turns trying to guess where the ships are. After a tutorial, you will play in a 6x6 board with 4 ships. The board is arranged in columns and rows where the columns use alphabetic letters A to F and the rows the numerals 1 to 6. After each turn you will issue a "shoot" command and specify the coordinates you would like to shoot at, for example: "shoot A 1". Alexa will reply with either "miss", "hit", or "sink" when a ship has been eliminated, that is, all its positions have been guessed. There is a battleship with 4 positions, a carrier with 3 positions, a submarine with 3 positions and a patrol boat with 2 positions. You win the game when all the ships have been eliminated.Try to exercise your memory by playing paperless and develop a strategy to eliminate all the ships in the minimum number of guesses! Larger boards will become available later.If you want to feel like you are in the navy (or you have trouble with the column letters), you can use greek letter names, the NATO or the Western Union phonetic alphabets (alpha, bravo, Charlie, delta, echo, Frank...)Icon: USS Iowa - United States Navy/Wikimedia Commons
title: Audio Battleship

author: by tommy sheu
commands: ['"Alexa, open Digit Guess."', '"The answer is one two three."', '"My answer is six three eight."']
description: Digit Guess 1A2B, also called "Bulls and Cows", is an addition game. Wikipedia description is available at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulls_and_Cows . It is an old-breaking paper and pencil game, now with voice version for Amazon Echo. Alexa generates a random 3-digit secret number. The digits are all different. You try to guess the number, and Alexa gives the matches. If the matching digits are in their right positions, they are "A", if in different positions, they are "B". Example:Secret number: 638Your try: 836Answer: 1 A and 2 B. (The A is "3", the B are "6" and "8".)
title: Digit Guess 1A2B

author: by Nathan Thompson
commands: ['"Alexa, start Go Sensei"', '"I place a stone at c7"', '"I\'ll play at f5"']
description: This skill will allow Alexa to play a game of Go against you.The game is played as the two of you take turns saying coordinates where you would like to place stones. You will go first and play as black. Alexa will go second and play as white. You will play on a 9 by 9 board with Japanese scoring rules. Komi is set at 5.5 for white.This skill uses Gnu Go (https://www.gnu.org/software/gnugo/) as the game engine and is distributed under the GNU General Public License (https://www.gnu.org/software/gnugo/gnugo_21.html#SEC210)Roadmap:- Allow the player to choose a color- Allow the player to choose a handicap- Allow the player to adjust Alexa's skill level- Allow for 13x13 and 19x19 board sizes- Allow the player to adjust the Komi- Allow the player to identify coordinates using the NATO phonetic alphabet- Allow the player to undo previous moves- Prevent the player from playing invalid movesNew features will be added based on input from the community. Vote for the features you want to see most:https://github.com/thompsnm/goSensei#roadmap-votingFeel like implementing a new feature yourself? See our Contributing guidelines:https://github.com/thompsnm/goSensei#contributing
title: Go Sensei

author: by Nathan Thompson
commands: ['"Alexa, start Go Sensei"', '"I place a stone at c7"', '"I\'ll play at f5"']
description: This skill will allow Alexa to play a game of Go against you.The game is played as the two of you take turns saying coordinates where you would like to place stones. You will go first and play as black. Alexa will go second and play as white. You will play on a 9 by 9 board with Japanese scoring rules. Komi is set at 5.5 for white.This skill uses Gnu Go (https://www.gnu.org/software/gnugo/) as the game engine and is distributed under the GNU General Public License (https://www.gnu.org/software/gnugo/gnugo_21.html#SEC210)Roadmap:- Allow the player to choose a color- Allow the player to choose a handicap- Allow the player to adjust Alexa's skill level- Allow for 13x13 and 19x19 board sizes- Allow the player to adjust the Komi- Allow the player to identify coordinates using the NATO phonetic alphabet- Allow the player to undo previous moves- Prevent the player from playing invalid movesNew features will be added based on input from the community. Vote for the features you want to see most:https://github.com/thompsnm/goSensei#roadmap-votingFeel like implementing a new feature yourself? See our Contributing guidelines:https://github.com/thompsnm/goSensei#contributing
title: Go Sensei

author: by 1step solution
commands: ['"Alexa, open Ocean Bottle"', '"Alexa, ask Ocean Bottle to make a new bottle"', '"Alexa, ask Ocean Bottle to pick up a bottle"']
description: Bottled messages date to about 310 B.C., in water current studies by Greek philosopher Theophrastus. In the sixteenth century, Queen Elizabeth I created an official position of "Uncorker of Ocean Bottles". In the nineteenth century, literary works such as Edgar Allan Poe’s 1833 “MS. Found in a Bottle” and Charles Dickens' 1860 "A Message from the Sea" inspired an enduring popular passion for sending bottled messages. In the year of 2017, Ocean Bottle, as an Alexa Skill, was launched in digital world on Amazon. Here, you can Throw a drifting bottle with your message to the ocean. Or pick up drifting bottles from the ocean, and reply to the sender if you want. The person who picked up your bottle, or the sender who received your reply, can reply back. In this way, the conversations keep going.How to use:To launch: “ Alexa, open Ocean Bottle. ” “ Alexa, ask Ocean Bottle to pick up a new bottle. ” “ Alexa, ask Ocean Bottle to make a new bottle. ” “ Alexa, ask Ocean Bottle to open reply. ”To throw a new bottle to the ocean: “ make” “ make a new bottle. ”To pick up a bottle from the ocean: “ pick up ”To reply a message or a bottle you just picked up: “ reply. ”To put message in the bottle or reply, just say the message: “ ( your message ) ”Once you receive a reply from the other side of the ocean, you can reply the new message immediately: “ reply ”Or skip it for now to reply later as an old message, by saying: “ next ”If you don’t want to continue a conversion anymore, you can say: “ delete ” or “ discard ”The conversion will never be on your new message or old message list.Of cause you can always get help by: “ help ”Or exist any time by: “ stop. ”Rules:1. You won’t pick up your own bottle.2. You won’t pick up the same bottle twice.3. Your reply to the bottle will be sent to the bottle maker, and they can reply back. In this way, the conversation will continue only between you two.We're always learning and building new features, and we can't do that well without your feedback. If you have suggestions, please share them with us at 1stepsolution.com@gmail.com.
title: Ocean Bottle

author: by Alexander King
commands: ['"Alexa, open Ancient Alchemy."', '"Combine \'water\' and \'fire\'."', '"What is my progress?"']
description: In Ancient Alchemy, you play the role of the Alchemist, and you have been charged with restoring the Library of Elements. The library once contained recipes for every element in the world. Start combining elements using primitive elements, and then continue on to document all elements in the world. The future rests upon your success.HOW TO PLAY:Your quest is to start by combining primitive elements: earth, water, air, and fire, to create more complex elements. Continue combining different combinations of all elements to re-create all elements that were once in the Royal Library of Elements. You can ask for details about elements as well as ask for recently found elements. All of the elements that you have found so far will be in your Alexa Scroll (Alexa App).TIPS:* You can hear the initial narrative of your quest by asking for a description of your quest* Ask for a hint once a day!* Continue combining elements to increase your title* You can compare your progress to others by asking for your progress* Once you have found an element, you can always ask to hear details about it.* When asking for recently found elements, you can find a full list of elements in your Alexa Scroll (Alexa App).FEEDBACK:If you love this skill, please leave a 5-start review! If, for any reason you don't think it deserves 5 stars, please email me your feedback alex@gotalex.com. I am also open to new ideas to make the experience better!ADDITIONAL INFORMATION:All icons licensed under Flaticon Basic License.
title: Ancient Alchemy

author: by Anstop
commands: ['"Alexa Bible Memory"', '"Alexa ask Bible Memory for Daily Promise"', '"Alexa ask Bible Memory to Study a Topic"']
description: Bible MemoryCategories Daily Promise Memorize a Verse Promises Challenge Topic Study Topic Challenge Read a VerseDaily Promise The Daily Promise will grab a random bible promise, read it two times, and ask you a series of questions on the verse.  1. What is the first word in the text?  2. What is/are the missing blank/blanks? a. 1 word missing over 5 characters. b. 2 words missing. c. 3 words missing. 3. Where is it found? Also if you answer book chapter and verse it will end right away.  a. book b. book and chapter c. book, chapter and verse Memorize a Verse This challenge will prompt you for a bible verse that you would like to memorize. It will then read it to you two times and ask you a series of questions on that verse.  1. What is the first word in the text?  2. What is/are the missing blank/blanks? a. 1 word missing over 5 characters. b. 2 words missing. c. 3 words missing. 3. Where is it found? Also if you answer book chapter and verse it will end right away. a. book b. book and chapter c. book, chapter and verse Promises Challenge The Promises Challenge will randomly grab 5 different bible promises. It will then read them one by one and ask you where each one is found. It will continue to ask a verse until you have answered where each one of them is correctly. Each attempt will count as 1 point. The perfect score is 5. When doing this challenge it is important to say the word verse between the chapter and verse.  1. Where is this verse found?  a. Looking for book, chapter and verse.  Topic Study Topic Study will help you memorize verses and bible locations of different topics in the bible and will help you study to do the Topic Challenge. This will read you one verse at a time for each of the verses in the topic. You can say Yes, No, or Repeat.  1. What topic would you like to study today?Topic Challenge Topic Challenge will prompt you for a specific topic. The app will then ask you if you would like to take on all of the questions for the topic. If you would like to do less that 15 you can say no and choose how many questions you would like. If you choose yes and the topic has more than 15 questions it will only grab 15 random texts withint that topic and quiz you on those. The app will ask on the location of each verse in that topic. It will start you off with a difficulty of easy and if you get 100% it will give you the option to up the next difficulty. This is the series of questions.  1. What topic would you like to memorize today? 2. Would you like to answer all the questions? a. Yes b. No = How many questions would you like?  3. Ask Questions  a. Easy difficulty  A. What is the book? You can actually say all of them as well. It will give you credit as long as you get the book right.  b. Medium difficulty A. What is the book and chapter? You can actually say all of them as well. It will give you credit as long as you get the book and chapter right.  c. Hard difficulty A. What is the book, chapter and verse? You must get all three correct.  4. 100% = The next level of difficulty will be ... Would you like to try it now? Please say yes or no.  < 100% = Would you like to try this bible memory challenge again? Read a Verse Read a verse is a simple bible reader. It will prompt you to choose a bible verse that you would like Alexa to read.  1. What verse would you like me to read? 2. Would you like to read this verse again?
title: Bible Memory

author: by Mark M Smith
commands: ['"Alexa, Start Memory Match"', '"row 1, column 2"', '"1, 2"']
description: Memory Match is a game where you try to match pairs of cards together in as few moves as possible. The twist is, you can't see the cards, so you have to keep it all in your head (or cheat with a piece of paper).You start with 12 cards face down, laid out in 4 rows of 3 columns. Each turn you first guess one card by saying "row 1, column 2" and you'll be told what's on the card, for example "red square". Next, you'll choose a second card, "row 4, column 1". If the second card matches the first they make a pair. Once you've figured out all 6 pairs, you win.Note: If you've turned on the 'start of request' tone in the settings for your Alexa device, you may experience problems with it recognizing your responses. You can switch it off by going to the Alexa app then Settings -> [your device name] -> Sound & Notifications and ensuring the switch for 'Start of Request' is in the off position (left, with the switch colored white).
title: Memory Match

author: by Ben
commands: ['"Alexa start Capital Quiz"', '"Alexa start Capital Quiz and open the Europe Quiz"', '"open the Worldwide Quiz"']
description: Test your knowledge and learn all the capitals of the world.You can start the Europe Quiz by saying "Alexa open Capital Quiz and start the Europe Quiz". Currently this quiz supports the following quiz types: Worldwide, Europe, Asia, America, Africa, Germany (federal states) and USA (federal states). You can also get the game modes by opening it first "Alexa open Capital Quiz" and then "give me the game modes". You get a general introduction by saying "help me".Once a quiz is started, you have the following request options:If you think that the current capital is Berlin, then you say "the answer is Berlin" or simply "Berlin". You can also answer "no idea" to jump to the next question. Alternatively you can also get a hint by saying "tell me the initial letter" or"give me some answers". If you want to hear the question again, just say "repeat the question". If Alexa misunderstood you, you can correct a wrongly declared answer by the sentence "correct the last answer". You get the current score by asking "how is the score?". If you want to change to another quiz, you can say "start the ... Quiz". For a detailed help during the game it is also worth to say "help me". With "Stop" you can end the Capital Quiz.Overview of requests to start a game:-Alexa start Capital Quiz-Alexa open Capital Quiz and start the USA Quiz (replace USA with desired game type)Overview of the commands in the game:-The answer is [capital]. (To answer the question)- [Capital] (answer the question)-Help (list of request options)-Tell me the current score-Repeat the question.-No idea! (Jumps to the next question)-Correct the last answer. (To correct a misunderstood answer)-Give me some answers.-Tell me the initial letter.-Start the [Quizname] Quiz.-Stop
title: Capital Quiz

author: by Wobble Mouth
commands: ['"Alexa Open Memory Flow"', '"Alexa ask Memory Flow to quiz me using easy sequences"', '"Alexa ask Memory Flow to use hard sequences"']
description: Memory flow is a skill that allows you to see how many words in a sequence you can remember, and then repeat those words back to me in the same order.  The sequence starts with one word. As you successfully repeat the word sequence back to me I will add a new word to the end of the sequence. The word sequence will continue to grow in length. I have a limit of up to 50 words in a sequence. There are three difficulty levels: easy, medium, and hard. For the easy difficulty level you can pick the type of words from choices of numbers, colors, animals, or names. For the medium difficulty level I will pick two types of words for you, and then make a sequence using those words. For the hard difficulty level I will pick words from any of the four choices, and then make a sequence using those words. At any time you can say stop, end, or cancel, and I will tell you how many words you were able to repeat back to me. So, let's try to remember, and play memory flow.
