author: by Dokka Inc.
commands: ['"Alexa, start Simon Says"', '"Alexa, open Simon Says"']
description: Simon Says is a game for 3 or more players where 1 player takes the role of "Simon" and issues instructions (usually physical actions such as "jump in the air" or "stick out your tongue") to the other players, which should only be followed if prefaced with the phrase "Simon says". Players are eliminated from the game by either following instructions that are not immediately preceded by the phrase, or by failing to follow an instruction which does include the phrase "Simon says". It is the ability to distinguish between genuine and fake commands, rather than physical ability, that usually matters in the game; in most cases, the action just needs to be attempted.The object for the player acting as Simon (In this case, Alexa) is to get all the other players (listeners) out as quickly as possible; the winner of the game is usually the last player who has successfully followed all of the given commands. Occasionally however, 2 or more of the last players may all be eliminated by following a command without "Simon Says", thus resulting in Simon winning the game.The game is well embedded in popular culture, with numerous references in films, music and literature.Reference: Wikipedia (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simon_Says)
title: Simon Says

author: by Musicplode Media Ltd.
commands: ['"Alexa, play Beat The Intro"', '"Alexa, ask Beat The Intro for Answers"', '"Alexa, ask Beat the Intro to Play It Again"']
description: Beat the Intro is the ultimate music game that tests your knowledge and love of music, while having a lot of fun in the process! It’s a game that all music fans have been playing forever without realizing – every time you hear a song on the radio, TV or leaking from someone’s headphones you can’t help but try and work out what it is. Well that’s Beat the Intro! We’ve developed this amazing new Skill from our Beat the Intro mobile game, which will test you against some of the greatest songs of all time, all with the help of Alexa and her knowledgeable music expert, Foxy! On your own or with a group of friends, Beat the Intro is the perfect play-along game. Ask Alexa to ‘Play Beat the Intro’, and between her and Foxy they will explain exactly what you need to do. There is a new game every day: a Six-Pack - work out the artist and title of six huge hits! - and TriplePlay - with three classic intros to crack before the singing starts, and if you really know your music then work out what the first line is! Currently we don’t allow Alexa to interrupt the songs, so you’ll have to wait until you’ve heard them all before you ask her and Foxy for the answers! We have exciting plans to evolve the Skill, and will be adding new and even more interactive games, so stay tuned! All that’s left to do is enable the Skill, play along, and enjoy yourself! If you ever get stuck, ask Alexa for ‘Help’ or read the card in the Alexa companion app. Beat the Intro with Alexa couldn’t be simpler, or more fun! What are you waiting for? 3… 2… 1… Let’s play!
title: Beat The Intro

commands: ['"Alexa open Word Chain"', '"Alexa tell Word Chain to resume"', '"Alexa ask Word Chain for my stats"']
description: Word Chain, also known as Grab on Behind and Last and First, is a game where two or more players take turns in saying words, where every next word should begin with the letter that the previous word ended.An example word chain is: Dog ~ Giraffe ~ Elephant ~ Tiger, and so on.You can play with Alexa and with other people around you as well. There are four different categories from which to choose: countries, capitals, animals, fruits and vegetables.The game can be played in cooperative and competitive mode. In cooperative mode our target is to build the largest possible word chain. you can skip turns, letting Alexa or other players guess a word. In competitive mode, if you cannot think of a word you are out of the game, your target is to be the last one in the game. It is recommended to master out cooperative mode, before going against Alexa, cause she knows quite a lot of words :-)[13 May 2017] As requested, Word Chain has a richer animals, fruits and vegetables vocabulary.
title: Word Chain

author: by TsaTsaTzu
commands: ['"alexa, play friday night poker"', '"alexa open friday night poker"', '"alexa ask friday night poker to deal"']
description: This is the historical implementation of five card draw poker. You are paired off against 3 other opponents. Every day you get an allowance of money you can bet with. As long as you have money, and you haven't completely fleeced all your opponents, you can play. Each day you play increases your daily allowance.You will be dealt five cards initially, and must bet based on those. If you don't like your hand, you can fold to give up. If you call, you must contribute chips to the pot at the current betting level. If you raise, you increase the betting level by one. Once everyone calls, you move on to the next phase.During the discard phase, you may discard up to three of your cards. You will receive new cards to replace them.As before, the betting starts again. If everyone else folds, you win by default. If the game is called, then all remaining players show their cards and the highest hand wins.
title: Friday Night Poker

commands: ['"Alexa, open Top-Grossing Films Trivia."', '"1962"', '"Next"']
description: Do you know the most popular film released in each year? Test your knowledge on the top-grossing films!This skill let's you walk down memory lane by asking you which year you want to visit. You are then given four films to choose from.More specifically, if you say "random", "next", or "previous", you will skip over years that you have already visited. You can also say "first" or "last" for the first or last year that you have not yet visited.You can even mark years as if you have visited them. For example, suppose you first say "mark years before 1990" and also "mark years after 2000". Then when you say "random", you will only be asked about a year from 1990 to 2000.You can specify a four digit year to visit, and also to revisit the year. For example, even after you say "mark years before 1990" as if you have visited them, you can still revisit 1989 by specifying "1989".Alexa will tell you when you have gotten two, five, and every ten questions correct. You can also say "my score" for your current score, or "stop" for your final score.

description: Magoosh Spelling Game is a fun, turn-based spelling game, where you can learn definitions and practice spelling 250+ GRE-level words. It's created by Magoosh test prep, an online company dedicated to providing students with fun and helpful educational materials.Just ask, "Alexa, launch the spelling game", and she'll ask if you want to start the game. She'll give you a word and you will then spell the word together, alternating letters. For example, she might say something like this:"The word is choleric. It means 'prone to outbursts of temper; easily angered'. The first letter is 'c'. What is the next letter?"You would then respond with 'h', and she would continue with 'o', and you would continue with 'l', and so on. Don't worry if you get a letter wrong! She'll ask you to repeat your answer in case she misheard you. If you get it wrong 3 times, Alexa will give you the correct letter and ask if you want to either start the word over or move on to a new word. And that's it! Have fun!Please leave any feedback below, constructive or positive, and we'll do our best to make this skill better for you!
